body:
&quot;Strawberry, pick ADC.&quot;

{{champion:90}} I&#039;m taking Malz, we need magic damage. (we had an ADC/Marksman top (Graves), and AD champs in mid and jungle. I chose a magic user to keep our damage type diversified)

&quot;No, you&#039;re ADC.&quot;

{{champion:90}} We already have an ADC. We don&#039;t need two.

&quot;Just go ADC Malz.&quot;

{{champion:90}} No, I&#039;m going Mage Malz.
_
We get in the game, and the entire match is more of this._

&quot;You&#039;re ADC!&quot;

{{champion:90}} No, our ADC is top. I&#039;m a Mage.

&quot;No he isn&#039;t, Graves called Top, he&#039;s not ADC!&quot;

/all &quot;Report Malz!&quot;

/all [Enemy team] Why?

/all &quot;Trolling.&quot;

/all {{champion:90}} They keep telling me to be ADC, but our ADC is top.

/all &quot;No he isn&#039;t, Graves called Top, not ADC!&quot;

/all &quot;Report Malz!&quot;

I just... please help me League community, are people really this god damn stupid that they can&#039;t tell the difference between a lane position title and a role title?
